        "other_parliamentary_business": [
            {
                "body": "The Government has responded to a public (paper) petition calling for a ban on new intensive poultry units. The petition was presented to the House of Commons by Ellie Chowns MP on behalf of residents of the United Kingdom.\nRead the petition and the Government's response (https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2025-03-03/debates/25030343000037/IntensivePoultryUnits)\nThe petition asks the House of Commons to urge the Government to introduce a ban on new intensive poultry units, to support farmers into transitioning out of the poultry industry and to encourage reduced chicken consumption to achieve more sustainable levels.\nIn response to the petition's request, the Government states it prioritises cleaning up rivers, seas, and lakes, including the River Wye. Efforts involve working with stakeholders including local MPs, farmers, and environmental NGOs to tackle pollution. All farms, including non-permitted poultry farms, are subject to the farming rules for water, slurry silage and agricultural fuel oil regulations, and nitrates regulations, which are inspected for compliance by the Environment agency. \nThe Department for Environment Food and Rural Affairs is consulting on national planning reforms to help farmers diversify and improve animal welfare. The Government commits \u00a35 billion over two years to support farming, enhance food security, and promote British produce in public sector catering. The Government is also undertaking work on planning reforms to support food production, diversification of income streams, and fair competition across supply chains.\nWhat are public (paper) petitions?\nA public (paper) petition is a petition to the House of Commons presented by an MP.\nFind out more about public (paper) petitions (https://www.parliament.uk/get-involved/sign-a-petition/paper-petitions/) \nGet involved in the work of the UK Parliament\nYou can also sign up (https://parliament.us14.list-manage.com/subscribe?u=098af33234df9814f59fb205f&id=6e29cb1262) to the UK Parliament newsletter for the latest information on how to get involved and make a difference. \n",
                "created_at": "2025-03-12T15:29:24.143Z",
                "subject": "Government responds to petition on intensive poultry units",
